parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
the ABS light illuminates
the brakes emit a burning smell
the brakes smoke
the wheels wobble or shimmy
the brakes drag
and the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brakes to overheat, leading to brake failure and loss of control.
symptoms: The brake caliper seizes
the brake caliper sticks
the brake caliper overheats
the brake caliper drags
the brake caliper leaks brake fluid
and the brake caliper causes the brake pads to wear unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The brake fluid leaks
the brake fluid is low
the brake fluid is contaminated
the brake master cylinder fails
the brake lines are damaged
and the brake hydraulic system overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose critical information about the vehicle's operation, such as speed, fuel level, and warning lights, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The instrument cluster display fails to turn on
gauges reset to zero
warning lights come on and remain on
the panel goes dark at night
buzzing alarm sounds
and the display blanks out intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pressure regulator can cause a significant fuel leak, which can lead to a fire hazard, explosion, or accident, especially if the fuel comes into contact with an ignition source.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the engine area
fuel spraying onto the ground
fuel soaking the carpet or interior of the vehicle
fuel smell inside the vehicle
wetness or fuel odor on the driver's foot or clothing.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Retaining Clip Failure on Fuel Pressure Regulator
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the retaining clip on the fuel pressure regulator can cause the fuel pressure regulator to malfunction, leading to a significant fuel leak and potential fire hazard.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the engine area
fuel spraying onto the ground
fuel soaking the carpet or interior of the vehicle
fuel smell inside the vehicle
wetness or fuel odor on the driver's foot or clothing.
